  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "However, few studies have explicitly measured 'prestige', thus contributing to the overall difficulty of conducting consistent and comparative occupation-level research.",
    "Despite its methodological drawbacks and age, modern research continues to rely on Treiman's (1977) Standard International Occupational Prestige Scale (SIOPS) as a key variable (e.g., Buchs et al. 2017; Chudnoyskaya and Kashap 2020; Lersch et al. 2020; Oesch and Piccitto 2019; Pitt and Zhu 2019).",
    "In addition, the U.S. General Social Survey (GSS) Occupational Prestige Module (Smith and Son 2014) has been adopted and analysed as a more up-to-date prestige index (e.g., Valentino 2020 Valentino, 2021)).",
    "Again, however, the GSS does not explicitly measure 'prestige' but 'social standing'.",
    "Occupational prestige is influenced by biases, power dynamics, and information availability."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Despite its methodological drawbacks and age, modern research continues to rely on Treiman's (1977) Standard International Occupational Prestige Scale (SIOPS) as a key variable (e.g., Buchs et al. 2017; Chudnoyskaya and Kashap 2020; Lersch et al. 2020; Oesch and Piccitto 2019; Pitt and Zhu 2019).",
    "In addition, the U.S. General Social Survey (GSS) Occupational Prestige Module (Smith and Son 2014) has been adopted and analysed as a more up-to-date prestige index (e.g., Valentino 2020 Valentino, 2021))."
  ]
